@NODE E1 "About..."

CyberGFXRenderer is a FrameBuffer PlugIn for LightWave 4.x.
It is used to display rendered pictures directly on a 16-Bit or 24-Bit
CyberGFX-Screen, so there is no need to load an external display program
or to use the low quality built-in display routines.

@ENDNODE

@NODE E2 "Requirements..."

All you need is Amiga-Dos 2.x or higher and LightWave 4.x.

@ENDNODE

@NODE E3 "Installation..."

Just copy "CyberGFXRenderer.p" to "Toaster:Programs/PlugIns/Layout" and add
it to the PlugIn Database.
In the RECORD Panel there should be a new Render Display called "CyberGFX".

Then start the Preferencesprogram to choose your screenmode.

The best and fastest screenmode is 800*600*16it !!


@ENDNODE

@NODE E4 "Control..."

After LightWave has finished rendering a picture, the selected CyberGFX-Screen 
will move to front displaying the picture.
To abort the displaying of the picture, just press ESC.
After the picture has been displayed, press ESC to quit the program and switch
back to the LightWave Render Screen.

@ENDNODE

